CATER 154664, Kly Mod 20-6: when station HV raised above 15 KV, CB 7 trips.
text: Kly Mod 20-6 (Gun): CB 7 trips when station gets above 15KV. Dayshift swapped the Enerpro board, 1 SCR block (phase control), and made close inspection of the downstream components. Don't know specifics of exactly what they did beside T20 swap. Swapped regulator board: no effect. The HVPS current and PFN volts waveforms show problems on the recovery--lots of fluctation on the tail end of the PFN recovery and the tail end of the HVPS current "hump". Swapped thyratron: waveforms much more stable now. In = 300153, out = 101280. MM = 13.7%. KA = 284 mA. Final eres = 3.65 volts. New HVPS set point = 17.1 KV. Amps = 3.15. After running up station with new thyratron to full set point of 17.1 KV, after a few minutes, we would hear a "BBBRRRRRTTTTT" sound that appears to have come from the 5 henry filter choke. We believe this was due to a problem with the DQing. After this sound, CB 7 would trip! Opened mod and checked DQ ckt: trigger cable and connections look good. The 3 filter caps on the DQ chassis measure good. SCRs appear good. Checked all wiring connections including shunt--all tight, no comprimised insulation. Next time we have a PAMM, may want to inspect the rooftop DQing resistors. Anatoly K. believes we still have a problem with the 3 phase controller--perhaps another bad SCR block. We ran station at full HV set with the DQ trigger cable disconnected--station runs fine with no trips. Connected trigger cable again and lowered DQ I to zero amps and slowly raised it--we brought it up to 11.5 amps and let it run for 20 minutes--no CB 7 trips, no "BBBRRRRRRTTTTT" sound. Called Howard at ACR and asked if we can leave this in this state--don't want to raise DQ any higher until engineers can determine why DQing current or the phase controller might possibly becausing this problem. Station on and running now. CATER ready to close in lieu of possible new CATER if we are dissatisfied with station ops. --dayshift, ps, ak, rm, sj
